Two reasons.

00:03:23.230 --> 00:03:29.370
One, as Krishna was mentioning,
the wisdom seems

00:03:29.370 --> 00:03:32.940
to be an area where we have
a lot to say about.

00:03:32.940 --> 00:03:35.240
In India, you know,
we are the source

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:37.590
of five major religions.

00:03:37.590 --> 00:03:43.640
But at the same time, many times
our approach to managing

00:03:43.640 --> 00:03:48.100
each other, managing oneself,
is more Western than even

00:03:48.100 --> 00:03:50.570
Westerners deal with.

00:03:50.570 --> 00:03:54.086
In some respects, it's like
we have a schism.

00:03:54.086 --> 00:03:58.220
During the daytime, we operate
in a Western way.

00:03:58.220 --> 00:04:03.290
But the moment the office hours
are over, the bhangra

00:04:03.290 --> 00:04:07.700
and the dancing and the fun
starts, and the prayers and

00:04:07.700 --> 00:04:11.670
the various other activities and
the rare festivals and the

00:04:11.670 --> 00:04:17.850
work and the life and the fun
seamlessly integrate.

00:04:17.850 --> 00:04:22.690
That one continuous integrity
that seems to be the source of

00:04:22.690 --> 00:04:28.740
energy, source of rejuvenation,
source of fun,

00:04:28.740 --> 00:04:33.830
is something that gives meaning,
that gives purpose,

00:04:33.830 --> 00:04:37.185
and that evokes passion for
us to be innovative,

00:04:37.185 --> 00:04:39.670
for us to be ingenuous.

00:04:39.670 --> 00:04:44.720
How do we tap into that, what is
the source of that, is the

00:04:44.720 --> 00:04:49.470
question which has been, really,
in my mind from the

00:04:49.470 --> 00:04:51.650
time I quit Apple Computer.

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:54.096
I was in Apple in international
marketing for a

00:04:54.096 --> 00:04:55.610
while in 1980s.

00:04:55.610 --> 00:04:57.050
I was in Apple University.

00:04:57.050 --> 00:05:00.360
I was the head of school of
technology and management in

00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:01.110
Apple University.

00:05:01.110 --> 00:05:04.690
And I was a research fellow
looking at future directions

00:05:04.690 --> 00:05:07.500
in how people learn, how people
think, how people

00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:10.680
create, how people relate,
how people lead.

00:05:10.680 --> 00:05:13.890
So this was in 1988, 89.

00:05:13.890 --> 00:05:17.470
With a friend and partner called
Bill Atkinson and more

00:05:17.470 --> 00:05:22.520
of a guidance from Alan Kay, we
began to think about how do

00:05:22.520 --> 00:05:27.180
we actually design tools that
augment human intelligence.

00:05:27.180 --> 00:05:30.600
I found out, after actually
spending a large amount of

00:05:30.600 --> 00:05:36.070
time investigating, inquiring,
and interviewing about 200

00:05:36.070 --> 00:05:38.390
extraordinary people,
including many Nobel

00:05:38.390 --> 00:05:42.530
laureates, brain researchers,
spiritual leaders,

00:05:42.530 --> 00:05:46.020
psychologists, sports
personalities.

00:05:46.020 --> 00:05:49.445
We came back, and we tried to
see whether we could create a

00:05:49.445 --> 00:05:52.970
prologue or artificial
intelligence systems to

00:05:52.970 --> 00:05:57.970
capture some of what makes
people energized, what makes

00:05:57.970 --> 00:06:00.595
people creative, what
makes people learn.

00:06:00.595 --> 00:06:06.350
None of them worked, because we
found out we can scale up

00:06:06.350 --> 00:06:11.170
mechanically elements
of human ingenuity.

00:06:11.170 --> 00:06:15.770
But what truly differentiates
each one from anybody else,

00:06:15.770 --> 00:06:19.540
what truly differentiates our
own innovation, our own

00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:23.430
approach to life, how we
contribute and how we

00:06:23.430 --> 00:06:23.810
[INAUDIBLE]

00:06:23.810 --> 00:06:27.940
become our own brands
is not easy to scale

00:06:27.940 --> 00:06:29.840
it up in that way.

00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:32.950
I'm sure you guys well
may prove me wrong.

00:06:32.950 --> 00:06:35.220
That is what I think in
more ways than one.

00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:38.330
From 20 years ago to now,
I see a lot of things I

00:06:38.330 --> 00:06:41.500
thought-- these are not
algorithmic, or they are not

00:06:41.500 --> 00:06:44.135
possible to be scaled up--

00:06:44.135 --> 00:06:48.580
I think Google has done a
significant increase in it.

00:06:48.580 --> 00:06:52.190
So at that time, we realized
there is something called

00:06:52.190 --> 00:06:55.460
learning that leads to
innovation and learning that

00:06:55.460 --> 00:06:57.090
leads to wisdom.

00:06:57.090 --> 00:06:59.810
One will allow us to do
a lot of things in

00:06:59.810 --> 00:07:01.640
the external world.

00:07:01.640 --> 00:07:07.090
One will give us a sense of
peace, happiness, serenity and

00:07:07.090 --> 00:07:10.090
equanimity to deal with
the external crisis.

00:07:10.090 --> 00:07:13.540
These two are front of the
hand, back of the hand.

00:07:13.540 --> 00:07:16.380
So when I quit Apple, I
thought I will do user

00:07:16.380 --> 00:07:17.430
interface design.

00:07:17.430 --> 00:07:19.470
That's where I thought I'll
get the consulting.

00:07:19.470 --> 00:07:22.890
But instead, we started getting
opportunities to do

00:07:22.890 --> 00:07:26.750
leadership development
and develop

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:29.000
adult education programs.

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:33.880
23 years later, when this book
came out, we realized what we

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:38.100
needed to document was some
good stories on how

00:07:38.100 --> 00:07:40.980
extraordinary people perform.

00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:45.750
And then, how smartness can
help us and hurt us.

00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:48.140
What are the differences
in smartness?

00:07:48.140 --> 00:07:51.450
Some people are great in
becoming domain experts,

00:07:51.450 --> 00:07:56.070
functional smart people who like
to stay within their box

00:07:56.070 --> 00:08:00.830
and go deep down as a hedgehog
and become somebody world

00:08:00.830 --> 00:08:04.350
renowned in their field of
expertise but are unwilling to

00:08:04.350 --> 00:08:08.240
take risks, but are unwilling
to look outside the box and

00:08:08.240 --> 00:08:10.060
have entrepreneurial sense.

00:08:10.060 --> 00:08:13.310
On the other side, there are
people who are willing to jump

00:08:13.310 --> 00:08:16.970
from one to another to another,
connect the dots, and

00:08:16.970 --> 00:08:22.400
go broadly, but always need help
in executing to go deep

00:08:22.400 --> 00:08:26.110
beneath the functional
smart people.

00:08:26.110 --> 00:08:29.380
So for anything to be
successful, we need some

00:08:29.380 --> 00:08:32.360
people who are great in
execution, some people who are

00:08:32.360 --> 00:08:35.010
great in business thinking,
if you want to call it.

00:08:35.010 --> 00:08:37.780
Together, they can
bring success.

00:08:37.780 --> 00:08:41.659
We've looked at it and said, why
do people keep on going on

00:08:41.659 --> 00:08:42.930
one end of the spectrum?

00:08:42.930 --> 00:08:46.090
We call it the blue end of the
spectrum, being the functional

00:08:46.090 --> 00:08:50.100
smart, red end of the spectrum
being the business smart.

00:08:50.100 --> 00:08:55.870
In between is the freedom,
is the place of wisdom.

00:08:55.870 --> 00:08:59.870
And that is what we have
been investigating.

00:08:59.870 --> 00:09:05.805
We interviewed people like Alan
Mulally of Ford, or Indra

00:09:05.805 --> 00:09:11.200
Nooyi, or Sam Palmisano of IBM,
and John Mackey of Whole

00:09:11.200 --> 00:09:16.165
Foods, in India, Narayana Murthy
of Infosys or Kiran

00:09:16.165 --> 00:09:18.735
Mazumdar of Biocon.

00:09:18.735 --> 00:09:21.990
And there are several people
in Tata Group.

00:09:21.990 --> 00:09:25.030
So we began to look at,
essentially, the story between

00:09:25.030 --> 00:09:26.780
the West and the East.

00:09:26.780 --> 00:09:31.630
It is like it's a book written
combining the wisdom of India

00:09:31.630 --> 00:09:34.730
and the wisdom of the United
States, a lot more.

00:09:34.730 --> 00:09:37.620
So based on those interviews,
we came up with

00:09:37.620 --> 00:09:39.770
a very simple framework.

00:09:39.770 --> 00:09:41.970
If you put it as an acronym,
to make it

00:09:41.970 --> 00:09:43.220
easy, we call it wisdom.

00:09:45.800 --> 00:09:49.540
In this book, we talk about
those six elements which are

00:09:49.540 --> 00:09:53.650
represented by each letter of
the acronym, working and

00:09:53.650 --> 00:09:58.130
acting with authenticity
and appropriateness.

00:09:58.130 --> 00:10:03.400
Looks like oxymoron, but we need
both of them to be wise--

00:10:03.400 --> 00:10:06.310
intelligent and flexible
fortitude--

00:10:06.310 --> 00:10:09.270
once you take on a project,
how long you stay with it,

00:10:09.270 --> 00:10:12.473
when do you let go, when do you
hold on, when do you move

00:10:12.473 --> 00:10:16.480
on, which requires certain
discernment.

00:10:16.480 --> 00:10:19.900
Shifting the perspective
from what I want

00:10:19.900 --> 00:10:21.460
to what others want--

00:10:21.460 --> 00:10:25.830
because these days of social
network, these days of how we

00:10:25.830 --> 00:10:28.240
are interconnected, Google+--

00:10:28.240 --> 00:10:31.020
when you look at it, it is not
what you do it that makes a

00:10:31.020 --> 00:10:34.360
difference but how many people
like what you do.

00:10:34.360 --> 00:10:38.330
And they amplify it, multiply
it, and begin to do something

00:10:38.330 --> 00:10:40.490
with some of these ideas.

00:10:40.490 --> 00:10:43.520
How many ideas that are floating
around in the world

00:10:43.520 --> 00:10:47.970
have originated in you that
other people kind of, what do

00:10:47.970 --> 00:10:49.830
you call, created a viral.

00:10:49.830 --> 00:10:50.470
That's important.

00:10:50.470 --> 00:10:55.230
So can I shift the perspective
from self-centered to

00:10:55.230 --> 00:10:59.640
other-centered before
decision logic?

00:10:59.640 --> 00:11:03.880
Do we know what part of our
important decisions are made

00:11:03.880 --> 00:11:14.200
by infusion, instinct, emotion,
or data, wherefore,

00:11:14.200 --> 00:11:16.530
openness to change the roles.

00:11:16.530 --> 00:11:18.185
Sometimes you are the boss.

00:11:18.185 --> 00:11:20.530
And on another project,
sometimes

00:11:20.530 --> 00:11:22.020
you are a team member.

00:11:22.020 --> 00:11:24.840
In some place, you are
the person who

00:11:24.840 --> 00:11:26.370
gives all the ideas.

00:11:26.370 --> 00:11:28.280
In some other project,
you are the person

00:11:28.280 --> 00:11:29.760
who needs to implement.

00:11:29.760 --> 00:11:33.840
But if you get stuck with one
role, saying, because I have

00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:38.060
been in this role, I always have
to be in that role, you

00:11:38.060 --> 00:11:40.800
get left behind.

00:11:40.800 --> 00:11:43.020
So the role clarity,
how do I play that?

00:11:43.020 --> 00:11:46.330
And finally, what are the things
you want for short

00:11:46.330 --> 00:11:50.120
term, medium term, long term,
and how do you become

00:11:50.120 --> 00:11:54.620
productive by discovering your
own drivers of motivation.

00:11:54.620 --> 00:11:57.550
These are six things which
we touched upon.

00:11:57.550 --> 00:12:02.550
And if you were to look at the
book, first we recommend, go

00:12:02.550 --> 00:12:06.610
check out a website where we
have a, what do you call--

00:12:06.610 --> 00:12:06.703
NAVI RADJOU: The assessment.

00:12:06.703 --> 00:12:08.100
PRASAD KAIPA: --the wise
leader questionnaire

00:12:08.100 --> 00:12:09.770
assessment.

00:12:09.770 --> 00:12:14.360
For these six wisdom acronyms,
each of them, we have created

00:12:14.360 --> 00:12:15.210
some questions.

00:12:15.210 --> 00:12:16.720
It takes less than
five minutes for

00:12:16.720 --> 00:12:18.030
you to fill it out.

00:12:18.030 --> 00:12:21.840
If you go to
fromsmarttowise.com, you can

00:12:21.840 --> 00:12:24.670
actually go take the assessment,
see where the

00:12:24.670 --> 00:12:27.870
baseline is, and get the
book and read one

00:12:27.870 --> 00:12:29.080
chapter at a time.

00:12:29.080 --> 00:12:30.730
Don't read the whole
book at one time.

00:12:30.730 --> 00:12:32.450
Read one chapter.

00:12:32.450 --> 00:12:34.940
See what you can take
and practice.

00:12:34.940 --> 00:12:38.050
Discuss with other people.

00:12:38.050 --> 00:12:40.150
Put it on Facebook what
you are doing.

00:12:40.150 --> 00:12:44.170
And discuss what other people
are looking at.

00:12:44.170 --> 00:12:47.410
In your own Google circles, what
are all the ways in which

00:12:47.410 --> 00:12:49.520
other people are thinking
about it?

00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:53.610
And then, once you feel like you
got it into your DNA, move

00:12:53.610 --> 00:12:55.770
on to the other one.

00:12:55.770 --> 00:12:58.520
So that is how we have
written the book.

00:12:58.520 --> 00:13:01.130
So I have given you just
broadly the framework.

00:13:01.130 --> 00:13:03.090
And I'll let Navi
say a few words.

00:13:03.090 --> 00:13:04.740
And then, we can take some
questions on that.

00:13:04.740 --> 00:13:05.420
NAVI RADJOU: Sure.

00:13:05.420 --> 00:13:08.310
I mean, Prasad did a great job
in terms of outlining the

00:13:08.310 --> 00:13:10.780
contours of this wisdom
framework.

00:13:10.780 --> 00:13:13.260
But essentially, in a nutshell,
something to kind of

00:13:13.260 --> 00:13:16.580
clarify, so wisdom for us
is the application of

00:13:16.580 --> 00:13:19.650
intelligence to serve
a larger purpose.

00:13:19.650 --> 00:13:22.530
So what we are saying is not
that you need to kind of dial

00:13:22.530 --> 00:13:25.470
down your smartness, but find
the kind of right purpose

00:13:25.470 --> 00:13:28.800
where you can apply it in a very
context-aware fashion.

00:13:28.800 --> 00:13:31.840
The second kind of piece of
definition of wise leadership

00:13:31.840 --> 00:13:35.840
is this balancing act between
action and reflection and

00:13:35.840 --> 00:13:36.950
introspection.

00:13:36.950 --> 00:13:39.402
So because what defines a lot
of smart leaders get carried

00:13:39.402 --> 00:13:40.360
away by action.

00:13:40.360 --> 00:13:43.140
And we're just talking to large
companies last 10 days.

00:13:43.140 --> 00:13:46.450
One of the big question they ask
us was, look, we have to

00:13:46.450 --> 00:13:48.870
meet shareholders' expectations,
quarterly

00:13:48.870 --> 00:13:50.400
returns are still important.

00:13:50.400 --> 00:13:52.290
So it's all about action,
action, action.

00:13:52.290 --> 00:13:54.920
But we were just talking to a
large IT service company.

00:13:54.920 --> 00:13:57.440
We were saying, look, you are
facing a lot of competition in

00:13:57.440 --> 00:14:00.600
the marketplace right now, where
if you only focus on

00:14:00.600 --> 00:14:03.730
action, which is how can we
reclaim our lost market share,

00:14:03.730 --> 00:14:07.100
you lose an opportunity to step
back a bit and to reflect

00:14:07.100 --> 00:14:10.330
and introspect, to figure out
what caused this downfall in

00:14:10.330 --> 00:14:14.380
the first place, and how can
we regain our past glory by

00:14:14.380 --> 00:14:16.630
reconnecting with our
authentic self?

00:14:16.630 --> 00:14:19.130
And that is often seen as
luxury, because we are all

00:14:19.130 --> 00:14:21.590
driven in real-time kind
of mode all the time.

00:14:21.590 --> 00:14:24.080
So I just want to kind of say
that essentially a nice way to

00:14:24.080 --> 00:14:27.480
remember wisdom is many of you
might be developers, you know

00:14:27.480 --> 00:14:29.086
the language C++.

00:14:29.086 --> 00:14:34.590
So think about wisdom being
S++, smartness plus, plus.

00:14:34.590 --> 00:14:36.980
So it's not about relinquishing
your smartness

00:14:36.980 --> 00:14:40.150
but applying your smartness in
a context-aware fashion.

00:14:40.150 --> 00:14:42.760
That's the first plus,
recognizing that contexts keep

00:14:42.760 --> 00:14:44.020
changing all the time.

00:14:44.020 --> 00:14:46.350
And then, make sure that you
apply your smartness with the

00:14:46.350 --> 00:14:48.880
right intent and right
motivation.

00:14:48.880 --> 00:14:50.990
Rather than saying, oh, I'm
going to show off how smart I

00:14:50.990 --> 00:14:54.450
am, it's more about how can I
use my smartness to serve a

00:14:54.450 --> 00:14:54.875
larger purpose.

00:14:54.875 --> 00:14:57.770
So in a nutshell, that's what
it is, smart-plus-plus.

00:14:57.770 --> 00:14:58.582
PRASAD KAIPA: Yeah.

