00:23:40.610 --> 00:23:43.390
marketplace or the environment
is very much based on a

00:23:43.390 --> 00:23:46.430
zero-sum game mindset,
that is, that the pie

00:23:46.430 --> 00:23:48.960
is of a fixed size.

00:23:48.960 --> 00:23:52.220
So unless I get a piece of it as
big as I can, I'm going to

00:23:52.220 --> 00:23:54.150
leave it to the company
direct.

00:23:54.150 --> 00:23:57.070
The wise leaders, they go
into a co-creation mode.

00:23:57.070 --> 00:24:00.340
In other words, they say, look,
I have the confidence to

00:24:00.340 --> 00:24:03.000
bring in the whole ecosystem
to actually

00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:04.070
co-create this pie.

00:24:04.070 --> 00:24:06.660
So the bigger I can make the
pie, and have the power to

00:24:06.660 --> 00:24:09.300
make it, then everybody
gets a bigger slice.

00:24:09.300 --> 00:24:10.910
So in a nutshell, that's what
we mean, enlightened

00:24:10.910 --> 00:24:11.950
self-interest.

00:24:11.950 --> 00:24:14.460
So for example, case in point,
Paul Polman, the CEO of

00:24:14.460 --> 00:24:17.790
Unilever, has set a goal to
double the company's revenues

00:24:17.790 --> 00:24:22.640
by 2020 while reducing
environmental impact by 50%.

00:24:22.640 --> 00:24:24.100
It's about doing
more with less.

00:24:24.100 --> 00:24:26.020
Now, is he doing it
out of altruism?

00:24:26.020 --> 00:24:28.160
He, himself, on record,
won't say no.

00:24:28.160 --> 00:24:30.030
This is enlightened
self-interest.

00:24:30.030 --> 00:24:32.800
Because if I save on natural
resources, I save on cost.

00:24:32.800 --> 00:24:35.470
And these cost savings I can
pass on to the customer.

00:24:35.470 --> 00:24:37.330
And then, the shareholders
are happy, right?

00:24:37.330 --> 00:24:40.540
So thinking in a more holistic
fashion, in a more systemic

00:24:40.540 --> 00:24:43.360
fashion, that is also the
hallmark of wise leaders,

00:24:43.360 --> 00:24:45.020
versus the smart leaders.

00:24:45.020 --> 00:24:47.180
They have a very fragmented
view of the boat.

00:24:47.180 --> 00:24:49.350
For them, it's like, doubling
revenues, I can

00:24:49.350 --> 00:24:50.570
crack the code on it.

00:24:50.570 --> 00:24:52.920
Oh, saving the environment,
let's ask the CSR

00:24:52.920 --> 00:24:54.350
department do that.

00:24:54.350 --> 00:24:57.300
But bringing them together,
bridging them and integrating

00:24:57.300 --> 00:25:00.190
that, that's really, in a way,
what is wise leadership about.

00:25:00.190 --> 00:25:05.370
PRASAD KAIPA: So to build on
